<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-12-07T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-12-07T05:00:00-05:00" n="1255" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1255">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">767.68119/12–745: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Ankara</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-12-07T12:00:00+02:00">December
                                    7, 1945—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 11:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1543. Embtel 1480, November 23, noon. Secretary General of Foreign Office
                            tells me that Turk Govt has now reverted to its original decision not to
                            make written reply for time being to our note of November 2 regarding
                            Straits and to leave matter on basis verbal interim reply of November
                            12.</p>
                        <p>In this connection Erkin mentioned Prime Minister’s statement to press
                            December 5 in which reference was made to US note.</p>
                        <p>Sent Dept as 1543; repeated London 140 and Moscow 117.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>